      • wrapInJAXBAcceptedSoapEnvelope

        private java.lang.Object wrapInJAXBAcceptedSoapEnvelope(java.lang.Object o)
        Takes an object and wraps it in an JAXBElement with declared type Envelope. If it is already a JAXBElement with this declared type, it just returns it. If it is an accepted envelope, it creates the corresponding JAXBElement to wrap it in. If it is something else, it wraps it in an Envelope from namespace http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/
        Parameters:
        o - the Object to wrap
        Returns:
        the wrapped JAXBElement
